Program Language Design Translation
C++ VS Ada Generics

The goal of this assignment was to explore the strengths and weaknesses of Ada generics and C++ templates. I examine the capabilities of each through a generic sorting routine passing different data types to them. Additionally, I research documentation and whitepapers regarding Ada generics and how to perform them legally. Below is the list of resources that aided my research and personal experiments.

Credits:
https://learn.adacore.com/courses/intro-to-ada/chapters/generics.html
https://www.adaic.org/resources/add_content/standards/05rm/html/RM-12-3.html
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26082055/ada-generic-package-usage-and-compliation-error-non-visible-declaration
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9856365/ada-compilation-does-not-contain-expected-unit
https://groups.google.com/g/comp.lang.ada/c/1gnTw4BjAec?pli=1
https://www.adaic.org/resources/add_content/docs/craft/html/ch12.htm
https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Ada_Programming/All_Chapters#Generics


Things to know:
There are 2 directories: Source and TestFiles.
Source contains the Ada programs and C++ program:
(sort object files)
sort_package.adb
sort_package.ads
test_sort
test_sort.adb
sort.cpp
sort

Run Ada program: ./test_sort
Run C++ program: ./sort ../TestFiles/test0
C++ can run 7 different test cases test0-test6. Run them accordingly.
See output below.
